summary: This is an FBI crime scene sign-in log from the search of Jeffrey Epstein's properties on July 6, 2019. It documents the personnel from various agencies who entered and exited the scene, indicating a multi-agency investigation.

events.title: Search of Epstein Properties
events.description: FBI and other law enforcement personnel conducted a search of Jeffrey Epstein's properties, as documented by a crime scene sign-in log.

locations: 9 East 71st Street, New York, NY (Epstein's Manhattan townhouse)
keyFacts: The document is an FBI crime scene sign-in log dated July 6, 2019.
The search location was 9 East 71st Street, New York, NY, which is Jeffrey Epstein's Manhattan townhouse.
The log shows personnel from multiple agencies (FBI, HSI, USSS) participating in the search, indicating a coordinated multi-agency investigation.
The document is part of the evidence from the investigation into Jeffrey Epstein's activities.
The sign-in times show the search operation spanned from early morning to evening hours.
